layout.ab:
Dividers:



 I. Colon;

 Colon of two black dots and three red dashes
                                    (in-between, above, below) (e.g., 3vab,5vb, 6rb);

 Colon of two black dots and four red dots
                                    (above, below and on both sides) (e.g., 3ra, 4va, 5ra, 6vb, 7ra, 8va, 9rab, 12rab, 21rab,
                                    24rab, 27rab);

 II. Nine dot asterisk (used throughout the
                                    Ms.);

 Four dot asterisk (e.g., 5vb, 17va);

 Red four dot asterisk with dashes above and
                                    below; used after the number indicating a homily (e.g., 25rb, 34rb, 41ra);

 III. Two nine dot asterisks (8vb);

 Three nine dot asterisks between two chains of
                                    alternating black and red dots (, ).
